HEADWORD: Deductible
<hw>De*duct"i*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Capable of being deducted, taken away, or withdrawn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not one found honestly <qex>deductible</qex>⟦br⟧
From any use that pleased him.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs.
Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Deducible; consequential.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deduction</ent>⟦br⟧
